body:
A duplicate of #1654 with additional commits that automatically address incorrect style, created by [Restyled][]. Since the original Pull Request was opened as a fork in a contributor's repository, we are unable to create a Pull Request branching from it with only the style fixes. The following Restylers [made fixes](https://restyled.io/gh/TokTok/repos/c-toxcore/jobs/1338240): - astyle - clang-format To incorporate these changes, you can either: 1. Merge this Pull Request *instead of* the original, or 1. Ask your contributor to locally incorporate these commits and push them to the original Pull Request
Expand for example instructions ```console git remote add upstream https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore.git git fetch upstream pull//head git merge --ff-only FETCH_HEAD git push ```
**NOTE**: As work continues on the original Pull Request, this process will re-run and update (force-push) this Pull Request with updated style fixes as necessary. If the style is fixed manually at any point (i.e. this process finds no fixes to make), this Pull Request will be closed automatically. Sorry if this was unexpected. To disable it, see our [documentation][]. [restyled]: https://restyled.io [documentation]: https://github.com/restyled-io/restyled.io/wiki/Disabling-Restyled --- This change isâ€‚[](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/1739)

commit.message:
Add new feature - topic lock

Group founders can now toggle a topic lock. When the lock is enabled
only the founder and moderators can change the topic. When disabled
anyone can change the topic

bug that made the sole testnet tcp relay connection status alternate from
online to offline. This will need to be reverted once we merge with the
mainnet, or when the TCP bug gets fixed

commit.message:
Remove unique nick restriction on groups

This was a poorly implemented feature that could theoretically
cause the group to break. In addition, it didn't really serve
a useful purpose, since peers can already be uniquely identified
via their public key

commit.message:
Fix group password validation issues

The password length is now included in packets along-side the password
in order to validate the exact length of the password. We also no longer
send an empty 32 bytes in some packets when no password is set

commit.message:
Small refactor for do_gca()

We now only run do_gca() every two seconds instead of spamming in every
messenger iteration. The only thing it does is check for and remove stales
which doesn't need to be done that often.

Small refactor for do_gca()

We now only run do_gca() every two seconds instead of spamming in every
messenger iteration. The only thing it does is check for and remove stales
which doesn't need to be done that often.
